lighter
------------------------------------------
Lighter is a kmer-based error correction method for whole genome sequencing
data. Lighter uses sampling (rather than counting) to obtain a set of kmers
that are likely from the genome. Using this information, Lighter can correct
the reads containing sequence errors.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.7-1
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  zlib0-1.3.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.44-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  make-4.4.1-2
  zlib-devel-1.3.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/mourisl/lighter

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/mourisl/lighter/archive/refs/tags/v1.1.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack lighter-1.1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./lighter-1.1.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/lighter-1.1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/lighter-1.1.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(lighter)
  /usr/bin/lighter.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/lighter.README
  /usr/share/doc/lighter/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/lighter/README.md

